.SH Description
.PP
This routine returns a string representing the \f[C]version\f[] of the
MPI library.
The \f[C]version\f[] argument is a character string for maximum
flexibility.
.PP
The number of characters actually written is returned in the output
argument, \f[C]resultlen\f[].
In C, a `0' character is additionally stored at
\f[C]version[resultlen]\f[].
The \f[C]resultlen\f[] cannot be larger than
(\f[C]MPI_MAX_LIBRARY_VERSION_STRING\f[] \- 1).
In Fortran, \f[C]version\f[] is padded on the right with blank
characters.
The \f[C]resultlen\f[] cannot be larger than
\f[C]MPI_MAX_LIBRARY_VERSION_STRING\f[].
.SH Note
.PP
The \f[C]version\f[] string that is passed must be at least
\f[C]MPI_MAX_LIBRARY_VERSION_STRING\f[] characters long.
.PP
\f[C]MPI_Get_library_version\f[] is one of the few functions that can be
called before \f[C]MPI_Init\f[] and after \f[C]MPI_Finalize.\f[]
